item.title: What goes in the Run.bat and Compiler for 508 client sources?
item.dc:creator: @bite_the_man bite the man
item.description:
@bite_the_man wrote:

Bite The Man, it isn’t depending on the source, it depends on how & where the folders are placed(/named)

rofl…dude the whole point of telling sources is to show what the files might be named…did u not see i mentioned that in my post? like for espeon sources one of the files is espeon or paladino one is paladino…so u could find out what the files would be named by what sourse…if u say paladino i could easily tell u a path becuase the main of it is in paladino/rs2[br][br][size=1]Posted on: June 12, 2009, 08:19:09 pm[/size][hr]@echo off
Title Pker-Time Compiler
cd …
“d:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_05\bin\javac.exe” -cp . -d ./Bin/ ./Bulby/./io/*.java
pause

item.dc:creator: @bite_the_man bite the man
item.description:
@bite_the_man wrote:

the above might work…but we are going to need to know what source u are useing…
becuase they need to know filepaths in order to compile…and difference sources have different file names and if comple.bat doesnt recognise file names it wont compile…so basically tell what source and it can be found.
